The paper discusses mechanism design and auctions, which are typically studied in the game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the application of the generalized second price (GSP) auction in various domains, which could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents a new model for understanding advertisers' preferences, which could be relevant to the sub-category of economics and computation (cs.EC).
